						<summary>

						<p>The inscription belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalladēva (I)</hi> and is <hi rend="bold">dated in Śaka 944, Dundubhi (= A.D. 1022).</hi> It registers a gift of lands made by Māchimayya to the temple of Mūlasthānadēva constructed by his younger brother Saṅkimayya at <hi rend="bold">Rōṇa.</hi> Saṅkimayya's father was <hi rend="bold">Āytavarmma</hi> born in the family of Brahmā (i.e., a Brāhmaṇa) and a resident of the <hi rend="italic">mahā-agrahāra</hi> Rōṇa.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.</hi> Vol. XIX, pp. 223 ff.<note n="49-1">The piece of stone</note>)</p>						

						</summary>
